    {
      id: "filipina-kemerdekaan-1946",
      langs: {
        id: {
          title: "Kemerdekaan Filipina (4 Juli 1946): Akhir Dominasi Amerika",
          desc: "Filipina memperoleh kemerdekaan penuh dari Amerika Serikat pada 4 Juli 1946, menjadi bangsa berdaulat setelah hampir setengah abad penjajahan Amerika pasca Perang Dunia II.",
          content: "<p class=\"mb-4\">Filipina secara resmi memperoleh kemerdekaan dari Amerika Serikat pada 4 Juli 1946, sebuah tanggal yang dipilih untuk menandai kehadiran panjang Amerika (karena coincides dengan hari Kemerdekaan Amerika), dengan terlepasnya Filipina dari dominasi Amerika setelah hampir setengah abad pemerintahan Amerika pasca Perang Filipina-Amerika berakhir pada 1902.</p><p class=\"mb-4\">Jalan menuju kemerdekaan Filipina dimulai dari Commonwealth Act of 1935 yang memberikan status 'Persemakmuran Filipina' dan berjanji kemerdekaan penuh setelah sepuluh tahun, namun Perang Dunia II (1941-1945) mengganggu kronologi tersebut ketika Jepang menginvasi dan menduduki Filipina, mengakhiri status Commonwealth dan pemerintahan sipil Filipina sementara.</p><p class=\"mb-4\">Setelah Jepang menyerah pada 1945, Amerika Serikat kembali ke Filipina dan terus menyiapkan transisi menuju kemerdekaan, dengan Manuel Roxas menjadi Presiden pertama Filipina yang merdeka pada tanggal proklamasi kemerdekaan tersebut, memulai era baru pemerintahan nasional Filipina yang sepenuhnya berdaulat.</p><p class=\"mb-4\">Meskipun secara teknis merdeka, Filipina tetap mempertahankan hubungan militer dan ekonomi yang erat dengan Amerika Serikat melalui berbagai perjanjian bilateral, termasuk kehadiran basis militer Amerika dan ketergantungan pada bantuan ekonomi Amerika, sebuah warisan dari periode colonial yang terus mempengaruhi hubungan Filipina-Amerika hingga kini.</p><p class=\"mb-4\">Kemerdekaan Filipina pada 1946 menandai transformasi Filipina dari status koloni menjadi bangsa merdeka, namun perjalanan Filipina menuju stabilitas politik dan pembangunan ekonomi yang berkelanjutan masih panjang, dengan berbagai tantangan internal (ketidakstabilan politik, pergolakan sosial, dan ketimpangan ekonomi) dan eksternal (pengaruh geopolitik regional dan global) yang terus membentuk sejarah dan perkembangan Filipina modern.</p>",
          source: "National Historical Institute Philippines",
          sourceUrl: "https://nhcp.gov.ph/independence-day-1946/",
          sourceSnippet: "NHCP — Philippine Independence July 4, 1946",
          source2: "Encyclopaedia Britannica",
          sourceUrl2: "https://www.britannica.com/place/Philippines/American-colonial-period-and-independence",
          sourceSnippet2: "Britannica — Philippine independence 1946",
          source3: "World History Encyclopedia",
          sourceUrl3: "https://www.worldhistory.org/article/2159/philippine-independence-1946/",
          sourceSnippet3: "WHE — Philippine Independence 1946"
        },
        en: {
          title: "Philippine Independence (July 4, 1946): End of American Dominance",
          desc: "The Philippines gained full independence from the United States on July 4, 1946, becoming a sovereign nation after nearly half a century of American rule following World War II.",
          content: "<p class=\"mb-4\">The Philippines officially gained independence from the United States on July 4, 1946, a date chosen to mark America's long presence (coinciding with American Independence Day), with the Philippines separating from American dominance after nearly half a century of American rule following the end of the Philippine-American War in 1902.</p><p class=\"mb-4\">The path to Philippine independence began with the Commonwealth Act of 1935, which granted the 'Philippine Commonwealth' status and promised full independence after ten years, but World War II (1941-1945) disrupted this timeline when Japan invaded and occupied the Philippines, temporarily ending Commonwealth status and Philippine civil government.</p><p class=\"mb-4\">After Japan's surrender in 1945, the United States returned to the Philippines and continued preparing the transition to independence, with Manuel Roxas becoming the Philippines' first president of an independent nation on the date of the independence proclamation, beginning a new era of fully sovereign Philippine government.</p><p class=\"mb-4\">Though technically independent, the Philippines maintained close military and economic relationships with the United States through various bilateral agreements, including American military base presence and dependence on American economic aid, a legacy of the colonial period that continued to influence Philippine-American relations to this day.</p><p class=\"mb-4\">Philippine independence in 1946 marked the Philippines' transformation from colonial status to a sovereign nation, but the Philippines' journey toward political stability and sustainable economic development was still long, with various internal challenges (political instability, social unrest, and economic inequality) and external factors (regional and global geopolitical influences) continuing to shape modern Philippine history and development.</p>",
          source: "National Historical Institute Philippines",
          sourceUrl: "https://nhcp.gov.ph/independence-day-1946/",
          sourceSnippet: "NHCP — Philippine Independence July 4, 1946",
          source2: "Encyclopaedia Britannica",
          sourceUrl2: "https://www.britannica.com/place/Philippines/American-colonial-period-and-independence",
          sourceSnippet2: "Britannica — Philippine independence 1946",
          source3: "World History Encyclopedia",
          sourceUrl3: "https://www.worldhistory.org/article/2159/philippine-independence-1946/",
          sourceSnippet3: "WHE — Philippine Independence 1946"
        },
        ja: {
          title: "フィリピン独立（1946年7月4日）：アメリカ支配の終焉",
          desc: "フィリピンは1946年7月4日にアメリカ合衆国から完全な独立を獲得し、第二次世界大戦後ほぼ半世紀間のアメリカ統治を経た後、主権国家となった。",
          content: "<p class=\"mb-4\">フィリピンは1946年7月4日にアメリカ合衆国から正式に独立を獲得し、この日付はアメリカの長い存在を示すために選ばれました（アメリカの独立記念日と重なる）、フィリピンはフィリピン・アメリカ戦争終結後のアメリカ統治からほぼ半世紀を経てアメリカ支配から分離しました。</p><p class=\"mb-4\">フィリピン独立への道は1935年のコモンウェルス法によって開始され、「フィリピン・コモンウェルス」の地位を付与し10年後の完全独立を約束しましたが、第二次世界大戦（1941-1945年）はこのタイムラインを混乱させました。日本がフィリピンに侵攻・占領し、コモンウェルス地位とフィリピン民間政府を一時的に終わらせました。</p>",
          source: "National Historical Institute Philippines",
          sourceUrl: "https://nhcp.gov.ph/independence-day-1946/",
          sourceSnippet: "NHCP — フィリピン独立1946年7月4日",
          source2: "Encyclopaedia Britannica",
          sourceUrl2: "https://www.britannica.com/place/Philippines/American-colonial-period-and-independence",
          sourceSnippet2: "Britannica — フィリピン独立1946"
        },
        ko: {
          title: "필리핀 독립 (1946년 7월 4일): 미국 지배의 종료",
          desc: "필리핀은 1946년 7월 4일 미국으로부터 완전한 독립을 얻었으며, 제2차 세계대전 이후 거의 반세기의 미국 통치를 거친 후 주권 국가가 되었다.",
          content: "<p class=\"mb-4\">필리핀은 1946년 7월 4일 미국으로부터 공식적으로 독립을 획득했으며, 이 날짜는 미국의 오랜 존재를 나타내기 위해 선택되었으며(미국 독립 기념일과 일치) 필리핀은 필리핀-미국 전쟁 종료 이후 미국 통치 거의 반세기를 거친 후 미국 지배로부터 분리되었습니다.</p><p class=\"mb-4\">필리핀 독립으로 가는 길은 1935년의 커먼웰스법으로 시작되었으며, 이는 \"필리핀 커먼웰스\" 지위를 부여하고 10년 후의 완전한 독립을 약속했지만, 제2차 세계대전(1941-1945)은 일본이 필리핀을 침략하고 점령하면서 이 일정을 방해했으며, 커먼웰스 지위와 필리핀 민간 정부를 일시적으로 종료시켰습니다.</p><p class=\"mb-4\">1945년 일본이 항복한 후 미국은 필리핀으로 돌아와 독립으로의 전환을 계속 준비했으며, 마누엘 록산이 독립 선포 날짜에 독립 필리핀의 첫 대통령이 되었고, 완전히 주권있는 필리핀 정부의 새로운 시대를 시작했습니다.</p>",
          source: "National Historical Institute Philippines",
          sourceUrl: "https://nhcp.gov.ph/independence-day-1946/",
          sourceSnippet: "NHCP — 필리핀 독립 1946년 7월 4일",
          source2: "Encyclopaedia Britannica",
          sourceUrl2: "https://www.britannica.com/place/Philippines/American-colonial-period-and-independence",
          sourceSnippet2: "Britannica — 필리핀 독립 1946"
        },
        zh: {
          title: "菲律宾独立 (1946年7月4日): 美国统治的终结",
          desc: "菲律宾于1946年7月4日获得美国的完全独立，在第二次世界大战后近半个世纪的美国统治后成为主权国家。",
          content: "<p class=\"mb-4\">菲律宾于1946年7月4日正式获得美国的独立，这个日期被选择以纪念美国的长期存在（与美国独立日相符），菲律宾在菲律宾-美国战争结束后经历了近半个世纪的美国统治，然后从美国统治中分离出来。</p><p class=\"mb-4\">菲律宾独立之路始于1935年的联邦法案，该法案授予\"菲律宾自治领\"地位并承诺十年后完全独立，但第二次世界大战（1941-1945）中断了这一时间表，当日本入侵并占领菲律宾时，临时结束了自治领地位和菲律宾民间政府。</p><p class=\"mb-4\">在1945年日本投降后，美国重返菲律宾并继续为独立过渡做准备，曼努埃尔·罗克萨斯在独立宣言日期成为独立菲律宾的首位总统，开启了完全主权菲律宾政府的新时代。</p><p class=\"mb-4\">虽然在技术上独立，菲律宾仍通过各种双边协议（包括美国军事基地的存在和对美国经济援助的依赖）与美国保持着密切的军事和经济关系，这是殖民地时期的遗留，继续影响着菲律宾-美国关系至今。</p>",
          source: "National Historical Institute Philippines",
          sourceUrl: "https://nhcp.gov.ph/independence-day-1946/",
          sourceSnippet: "NHCP — 菲律宾独立1946年7月4日",
          source2: "Encyclopaedia Britannica",
          sourceUrl2: "https://www.britannica.com/place/Philippines/American-colonial-period-and-independence",
          sourceSnippet2: "Britannica — 菲律宾独立1946"
        }
      }
    }
